IAO_0000115: A sequence_feature with an extent greater than zero. A nucleotide region is composed of bases and a polypeptide region is composed of amino acids.
label: region

IAO_0000115: A folded sequence.
label: sequence_secondary_structure

IAO_0000115: G-quartets are unusual nucleic acid structures consisting of a planar arrangement where each guanine is hydrogen bonded by hoogsteen pairing to another guanine in the quartet.
label: G_quartet

IAO_0000115: The many tandem repeats (identical or related) of a short basic repeating unit; many have a base composition or other property different from the genome average that allows them to be separated from the bulk (main band) genomic DNA.
label: satellite_DNA

IAO_0000115: A region amplified by a PCR reaction.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. This term is now located in OBI, with the following ID OBI_0000406.
label: PCR_product

IAO_0000115: One of a pair of sequencing reads in which the two members of the pair are related by originating at either end of a clone insert.
label: read_pair

IAO_0000115: The primary transcript of any one of several small cytoplasmic RNA molecules present in the cytoplasm and sometimes nucleus of a Eukaryote.
label: scRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A small non coding RNA sequence, present in the cytoplasm.
label: scRNA

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters required for the correct positioning of the polymerase for the start of transcription. Overlaps the TSS. The mammalian consensus sequence is YYAN(T|A)YY; the Drosophila consensus sequence is TCA(G|T)t(T|C). In each the A is at position +1 with respect to the TSS. Functionally similar to the TATA box element.
comment: Binds TAF1, TAF2.
label: INR_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters; Positioned from +28 to +32 with respect to the TSS (+1). Experimental results suggest that the DPE acts in conjunction with the INR_motif to provide a binding site for TFIID in the absence of a TATA box to mediate transcription of TATA-less promoters. Consensus sequence (A|G)G(A|T)(C|T)(G|A|C).
comment: Binds TAF6, TAF9.
label: DPE_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, located immediately upstream of some TATA box elements at -37 to -32 with respect to the TSS (+1). Consensus sequence is (G|C)(G|C)(G|A)CGCC. Binds TFIIB.
comment: Binds TFIIB.
label: BREu_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of the promoters of snRNA genes transcribed by RNA polymerase II or by RNA polymerase III. Located between -45 and -60 relative to the TSS. The human PSE_motif consensus sequence is TCACCNTNA(C|G)TNAAAAG(T|G).
label: PSE_motif

IAO_0000115: A group of loci that can be grouped in a linear order representing the different degrees of linkage among the genes concerned.
label: linkage_group

IAO_0000115: A region of double stranded RNA where the bases do not conform to WC base pairing. The loop is closed on both sides by canonical base pairing. If the interruption to base pairing occurs on one strand only, it is known as a bulge.
label: RNA_internal_loop

IAO_0000115: An internal RNA loop where one of the strands includes more bases than the corresponding region on the other strand.
label: asymmetric_RNA_internal_loop

IAO_0000115: A region forming a motif, composed of adenines, where the minor groove edges are inserted into the minor groove of another helix.
label: A_minor_RNA_motif

IAO_0000115: The kink turn (K-turn) is an RNA structural motif that creates a sharp (~120 degree) bend between two continuous helices.
label: K_turn_RNA_motif

IAO_0000115: A loop in ribosomal RNA containing the sites of attack for ricin and sarcin.
label: sarcin_like_RNA_motif

IAO_0000115: An internal RNA loop where the extent of the loop on both stands is the same size.
label: symmetric_RNA_internal_loop

IAO_0000115: The canonical base pair, where two bases interact via WC edges, with glycosidic bonds oriented cis relative to the axis of orientation.
label: WC_base_pair

IAO_0000115: A type of non-canonical base-pairing.
label: sugar_edge_base_pair

IAO_0000115: DNA or RNA molecules that have been selected from random pools based on their ability to bind other molecules.
label: aptamer

IAO_0000115: DNA molecules that have been selected from random pools based on their ability to bind other molecules.
label: DNA_aptamer

IAO_0000115: RNA molecules that have been selected from random pools based on their ability to bind other molecules.
label: RNA_aptamer

IAO_0000115: Morpholino oligos are synthesized from four different Morpholino subunits, each of which contains one of the four genetic bases (A, C, G, T) linked to a 6-membered morpholine ring. Eighteen to 25 subunits of these four subunit types are joined in a specific order by non-ionic phosphorodiamidate intersubunit linkages to give a Morpholino.
label: morpholino_oligo

IAO_0000115: A riboswitch is a part of an mRNA that can act as a direct sensor of small molecules to control their own expression. A riboswitch is a cis element in the 5' end of an mRNA, that acts as a direct sensor of metabolites.
label: riboswitch

IAO_0000115: A DNA region that is required for the binding of chromatin to the nuclear matrix.
label: matrix_attachment_site

IAO_0000115: A DNA region that includes DNAse hypersensitive sites located 5' to a gene that confers the high-level, position-independent, and copy number-dependent expression to that gene.
label: locus_control_region

IAO_0000115: A collection of match parts.
label: match_set

IAO_0000115: A part of a match, for example an hsp from blast is a match_part.
label: match_part

IAO_0000115: A clone of a DNA region of a genome.
label: genomic_clone

IAO_0000115: An operation that can be applied to a sequence, that results in a change.
label: sequence_operation

IAO_0000115: An attribute of a pseudogene (SO:0000336).
label: pseudogene_attribute

IAO_0000115: A pseudogene created via retrotranposition of the mRNA of a functional protein-coding parent gene followed by accumulation of deleterious mutations lacking introns and promoters, often including a polyA tail.
comment: Please not the synonym R psi M uses the spelled out form of the greek letter.
label: processed_pseudogene

IAO_0000115: A pseudogene caused by unequal crossing over at recombination.
label: pseudogene_by_unequal_crossing_over

IAO_0000115: To remove a subsection of sequence.
label: delete

IAO_0000115: To insert a subsection of sequence.
label: insert

IAO_0000115: To invert a subsection of sequence.
label: invert

IAO_0000115: To substitute a subsection of sequence for another.
label: substitute

IAO_0000115: To translocate a subsection of sequence.
label: translocate

IAO_0000115: A part of a gene, that has no other route in the ontology back to region. This concept is necessary for logical inference as these parts must have the properties of region. It also allows us to associate all the parts of genes with a gene.
label: gene_part

IAO_0000115: A DNA sequence used experimentally to detect the presence or absence of a complementary nucleic acid.
label: probe

IAO_0000115: A sequence_variant_effect which changes the regulatory region of a gene.
comment: OBSOLETE: This term was deleted as it conflated more than one term. The alteration is separate from the effect.
label: sequence_variant_affecting_regulatory_region

IAO_0000115: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number.
label: aneuploid

IAO_0000115: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number as extra chromosomes are present.
label: hyperploid

IAO_0000115: A kind of chromosome variation where the chromosome complement is not an exact multiple of the haploid number as some chromosomes are missing.
label: hypoploid

IAO_0000115: A regulatory element of an operon to which activators or repressors bind thereby effecting translation of genes in that operon.
label: operator

IAO_0000115: A binding site that, of a nucleotide molecule, that interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues of a nuclease.
label: nuclease_binding_site

comment: FLAG - this term is should probably be a part of rather than an is_a.
label: compound_chromosome_arm

IAO_0000115: A binding site that, in the nucleotide molecule, interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues of a restriction enzyme.
comment: A region of a molecule that binds to a restriction enzyme.
label: restriction_enzyme_binding_site

IAO_0000115: An intrachromosomal transposition whereby a translocation in which one of the four broken ends loses a segment before re-joining.
label: deficient_intrachromosomal_transposition

IAO_0000115: An interchromosomal transposition whereby a translocation in which one of the four broken ends loses a segment before re-joining.
label: deficient_interchromosomal_transposition

comment: This classes of attributes was added by MA to allow the broad description of genes based on qualities of the transcript(s). A product of SO meeting 2004.
label: gene_by_transcript_attribute

IAO_0000115: A chromosome structure variation whereby an arm exists as an individual chromosome element.
label: free_chromosome_arm

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a gene that has a sequence that overlaps the sequence of another gene.
label: overlapping

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when it is located within the intron of another gene.
label: inside_intron

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when it is located within the intron of another gene and on the opposite strand.
label: inside_intron_antiparallel

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when it is located within the intron of another gene and on the same strand.
label: inside_intron_parallel

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when the five prime region overlaps with another gene's 3' region.
label: five_prime_three_prime_overlap

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when the five prime region overlaps with another gene's five prime region.
label: five_prime_five_prime_overlap

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when the 3' region overlaps with another gene's 3' region.
label: three_prime_three_prime_overlap

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a gene when the 3' region overlaps with another gene's 5' region.
label: three_prime_five_prime_overlap

IAO_0000115: A region sequence that is complementary to a sequence of messenger RNA.
label: antisense

IAO_0000115: A transcript that is polycistronic.
label: polycistronic_transcript

IAO_0000115: A transcript that is dicistronic.
label: dicistronic_transcript

IAO_0000115: A gene from nuclear sequence.
label: nuclear_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene located in mitochondrial sequence.
label: mt_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene located in kinetoplast sequence.
label: kinetoplast_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from plastid sequence.
label: plastid_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from apicoplast sequence.
label: apicoplast_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from chloroplast sequence.
label: ct_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from chromoplast_sequence.
label: chromoplast_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from cyanelle sequence.
label: cyanelle_gene

IAO_0000115: A plastid gene from leucoplast sequence.
label: leucoplast_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from proplastid sequence.
label: proplastid_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from nucleomorph sequence.
label: nucleomorph_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from plasmid sequence.
label: plasmid_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene from proviral sequence.
label: proviral_gene

IAO_0000115: A proviral gene with origin endogenous retrovirus.
label: endogenous_retroviral_gene

IAO_0000115: A transposon or insertion sequence. An element that can insert in a variety of DNA sequences.
label: transposable_element

IAO_0000115: A match to an EST or cDNA sequence.
label: expressed_sequence_match

IAO_0000115: The end of the clone insert.
label: clone_insert_end

IAO_0000115: A sequence of amino acids linked by peptide bonds which may lack appreciable tertiary structure and may not be liable to irreversible denaturation.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology. The term 'protein' was merged with 'polypeptide'. Although 'protein' was a sequence_attribute and therefore meant to describe the quality rather than an actual feature, it was being used erroneously. It is replaced by 'peptidyl' as the polymer attribute.
label: polypeptide

IAO_0000115: A region of the chromosome between the centromere and the telomere. Human chromosomes have two arms, the p arm (short) and the q arm (long) which are separated from each other by the centromere.
label: chromosome_arm

IAO_0000115: An mRNA with a frameshift.
label: mRNA_with_frameshift

IAO_0000115: A sequence_variant is a non exact copy of a sequence_feature or genome exhibiting one or more sequence_alteration.
label: sequence_variant_obs

IAO_0000115: Any extent of continuous biological sequence.
label: sequence_feature

IAO_0000115: A gene encoded within a transposable element. For example gag, int, env and pol are the transposable element genes of the TY element in yeast.
label: transposable_element_gene

IAO_0000115: An oligo to which new deoxyribonucleotides can be added by DNA polymerase.
label: primer

IAO_0000115: A viral sequence which has integrated into a host genome.
label: proviral_region

IAO_0000115: A methylated deoxy-cytosine.
label: methylated_cytosine

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a sequence that is modified by editing.
label: edited

IAO_0000115: A transcript with a translational frameshift.
label: transcript_with_translational_frameshift

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe a sequence that is regulated.
label: regulated

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript that, at least in part, encodes one or more proteins.
comment: May contain introns.
label: protein_coding_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: forward_primer

IAO_0000115: A folded RNA sequence.
label: RNA_sequence_secondary_structure

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated at transcription.
comment: By:<protein_id>.
label: transcriptionally_regulated

IAO_0000115: Expressed in relatively constant amounts without regard to cellular environmental conditions such as the concentration of a particular substrate.
label: transcriptionally_constitutive

IAO_0000115: An inducer molecule is required for transcription to occur.
label: transcriptionally_induced

IAO_0000115: A repressor molecule is required for transcription to stop.
label: transcriptionally_repressed

IAO_0000115: A gene that is silenced.
label: silenced_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene that is silenced by DNA modification.
label: gene_silenced_by_DNA_modification

IAO_0000115: A gene that is silenced by DNA methylation.
label: gene_silenced_by_DNA_methylation

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated after it has been translated.
label: post_translationally_regulated

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a gene that is regulated as it is translated.
label: translationally_regulated

IAO_0000115: A single stranded oligo used for polymerase chain reaction.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: reverse_primer

IAO_0000115: This attribute describes a gene where heritable changes other than those in the DNA sequence occur. These changes include: modification to the DNA (such as DNA methylation, the covalent modification of cytosine), and post-translational modification of histones.
label: epigenetically_modified

IAO_0000115: Imprinted genes are epigenetically modified genes that are expressed monoallelically according to their parent of origin.
label: genomically_imprinted

IAO_0000115: The maternal copy of the gene is modified, rendering it transcriptionally silent.
label: maternally_imprinted

IAO_0000115: The paternal copy of the gene is modified, rendering it transcriptionally silent.
label: paternally_imprinted

IAO_0000115: Allelic exclusion is a process occurring in diploid organisms, where a gene is inactivated and not expressed in that cell.
comment: Examples are x-inactivation and immunoglobulin formation.
label: allelically_excluded

IAO_0000115: An epigenetically modified gene, rearranged at the DNA level.
label: gene_rearranged_at_DNA_level

IAO_0000115: Region in mRNA where ribosome assembles.
label: ribosome_entry_site

IAO_0000115: A sequence segment located within the five prime end of an mRNA that causes premature termination of translation.
label: attenuator

IAO_0000115: The sequence of DNA located either at the end of the transcript that causes RNA polymerase to terminate transcription.
label: terminator

IAO_0000115: A folded DNA sequence.
label: DNA_sequence_secondary_structure

IAO_0000115: A region of known length which may be used to manufacture a longer region.
label: assembly_component

IAO_0000115: A codon that has been redefined at translation. The redefinition may be as a result of translational bypass, translational frameshifting or stop codon readthrough.
label: recoded_codon

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing when a sequence, usually an mRNA is capped by the addition of a modified guanine nucleotide at the 5' end.
label: capped

IAO_0000115: A region of the transcript sequence within a gene which is not removed from the primary RNA transcript by RNA splicing.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: exon

IAO_0000115: One or more contigs that have been ordered and oriented using end-read information. Contains gaps that are filled with N's.
label: supercontig

IAO_0000115: A contiguous sequence derived from sequence assembly. Has no gaps, but may contain N's from unavailable bases.
label: contig

IAO_0000115: A sequence obtained from a single sequencing experiment. Typically a read is produced when a base calling program interprets information from a chromatogram trace file produced from a sequencing machine.
label: read

IAO_0000115: A piece of DNA that has been inserted in a vector so that it can be propagated in a host bacterium or some other organism.
label: clone

IAO_0000115: Yeast Artificial Chromosome, a vector constructed from the telomeric, centromeric, and replication origin sequences needed for replication in yeast cells.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: YAC

IAO_0000115: Bacterial Artificial Chromosome, a cloning vector that can be propagated as mini-chromosomes in a bacterial host.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: BAC

IAO_0000115: The P1-derived artificial chromosome are DNA constructs that are derived from the DNA of P1 bacteriophage. They can carry large amounts (about 100-300 kilobases) of other sequences for a variety of bioengineering purposes. It is one type of vector used to clone DNA fragments (100- to 300-kb insert size; average, 150 kb) in Escherichia coli cells.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology. Drosophila melanogaster PACs carry an average insert size of 80 kb. The library represents a 6-fold coverage of the genome.
label: PAC

IAO_0000115: A self replicating, using the hosts cellular machinery, often circular nucleic acid molecule that is distinct from a chromosome in the organism.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: plasmid

IAO_0000115: A cloning vector that is a hybrid of lambda phages and a plasmid that can be propagated as a plasmid or packaged as a phage,since they retain the lambda cos sites.
comment: Paper: vans GA et al. High efficiency vectors for cosmid microcloning and genomic analysis. Gene 1989; 79(1):9-20. This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: cosmid

IAO_0000115: A plasmid which carries within its sequence a bacteriophage replication origin. When the host bacterium is infected with "helper" phage, a phagemid is replicated along with the phage DNA and packaged into phage capsids.
label: phagemid

IAO_0000115: A cloning vector that utilizes the E. coli F factor.
comment: Birren BW et al. A human chromosome 22 fosmid resource: mapping and analysis of 96 clones. Genomics 1996.
label: fosmid

IAO_0000115: The point at which one or more contiguous nucleotides were excised.
label: deletion

IAO_0000115: A linear clone derived from lambda bacteriophage. The genes involved in the lysogenic pathway are removed from the from the viral DNA. Up to 25 kb of foreign DNA can then be inserted into the lambda genome.
label: lambda_clone

IAO_0000115: A modified  base in which adenine has been methylated.
label: methylated_adenine

IAO_0000115: Consensus region of primary transcript bordering junction of splicing. A region that overlaps exactly 2 base and adjacent_to splice_junction.
comment: With spliceosomal introns, the splice sites bind the spliceosomal machinery.
label: splice_site

IAO_0000115: Intronic 2 bp region bordering the exon, at the 5' edge of the intron. A splice_site that is downstream_adjacent_to exon and starts intron.
label: five_prime_cis_splice_site

IAO_0000115: Intronic 2 bp region bordering the exon, at the 3' edge of the intron. A splice_site that is upstream_adjacent_to exon and finishes intron.
label: three_prime_cis_splice_site

IAO_0000115: A cis-acting sequence that increases the utilization of (some) eukaryotic promoters, and can function in either orientation and in any location (upstream or downstream) relative to the promoter.
comment: An enhancer may participate in an enhanceosome GO:0034206. A protein-DNA complex formed by the association of a distinct set of general and specific transcription factors with a region of enhancer DNA. The cooperative assembly of an enhanceosome confers specificity of transcriptional regulation. This comment is a place holder should we start to make cross products with GO.
label: enhancer

IAO_0000115: An enhancer bound by a factor.
label: enhancer_bound_by_factor

IAO_0000115: A regulatory_region composed of the TSS(s) and binding sites for TF_complexes of the basal transcription machinery.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology. The region on a DNA molecule involved in RNA polymerase binding to initiate transcription.
label: promoter

IAO_0000115: A specific nucleotide sequence of DNA at or near which a particular restriction enzyme cuts the DNA.
label: restriction_enzyme_cut_site

IAO_0000115: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase I binds, to begin transcription.
label: RNApol_I_promoter

IAO_0000115: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase II binds, to begin transcription.
label: RNApol_II_promoter

IAO_0000115: A DNA sequence in eukaryotic DNA to which RNA polymerase III binds, to begin transcription.
label: RNApol_III_promoter

IAO_0000115: Part of a conserved sequence located about 75-bp upstream of the start point of eukaryotic transcription units which may be involved in RNA polymerase binding; consensus=GG(C|T)CAATCT.
label: CAAT_signal

IAO_0000115: A conserved GC-rich region located upstream of the start point of eukaryotic transcription units which may occur in multiple copies or in either orientation; consensus=GGGCGG.
label: GC_rich_promoter_region

IAO_0000115: A conserved AT-rich septamer found about 25-bp before the start point of many eukaryotic RNA polymerase II transcript units; may be involved in positioning the enzyme for correct initiation; consensus=TATA(A|T)A(A|T).
comment: Binds TBP.
label: TATA_box

IAO_0000115: A conserved region about 10-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units which may be involved in binding RNA polymerase; consensus=TAtAaT. This region is associated with sigma factor 70.
label: minus_10_signal

IAO_0000115: A conserved hexamer about 35-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units; consensus=TTGACa or TGTTGACA. This region is associated with sigma factor 70.
label: minus_35_signal

IAO_0000115: A nucleotide match against a sequence from another organism.
label: cross_genome_match

IAO_0000115: A group of contiguous genes transcribed as a single (polycistronic) mRNA from a single regulatory region.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: operon

IAO_0000115: The start of the clone insert.
label: clone_insert_start

IAO_0000115: A transposable element that is incorporated into a chromosome by a mechanism that requires reverse transcriptase.
label: retrotransposon

IAO_0000115: A match against a translated sequence.
label: translated_nucleotide_match

IAO_0000115: A transposon where the mechanism of transposition is via a DNA intermediate.
label: DNA_transposon

IAO_0000115: A region of the gene which is not transcribed.
label: non_transcribed_region

IAO_0000115: A major type of spliceosomal intron spliced by the U2 spliceosome, that includes U1, U2, U4/U6 and U5 snRNAs.
comment: May have either GT-AG or AT-AG 5' and 3' boundaries.
label: U2_intron

IAO_0000115: A transcript that in its initial state requires modification to be functional.
label: primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A retrotransposon flanked by long terminal repeat sequences.
label: LTR_retrotransposon

IAO_0000115: A group of characterized repeat sequences.
label: repeat_family

IAO_0000115: A region of a primary transcript that is transcribed, but removed from within the transcript by splicing together the sequences (exons) on either side of it.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: intron

IAO_0000115: A retrotransposon without long terminal repeat sequences.
label: non_LTR_retrotransposon

IAO_0000115: A DNA fragment used as a reagent to detect the polymorphic genomic loci by hybridizing against the genomic DNA digested with a given restriction enzyme.
label: RFLP_fragment

IAO_0000115: A dispersed repeat family with many copies, each from 1 to 6 kb long. New elements are generated by retroposition of a transcribed copy. Typically the LINE contains 2 ORF's one of which is reverse transcriptase, and 3'and 5' direct repeats.
label: LINE_element

IAO_0000115: An exon whereby at least one base is part of a codon (here, 'codon' is inclusive of the stop_codon).
label: coding_exon

IAO_0000115: The sequence of the five_prime_coding_exon that codes for protein.
label: five_prime_coding_exon_coding_region

IAO_0000115: The sequence of the three_prime_coding_exon that codes for protein.
label: three_prime_coding_exon_coding_region

IAO_0000115: An exon that does not contain any codons.
label: noncoding_exon

IAO_0000115: A region of nucleotide sequence that has translocated to a new position. The observed adjacency of two previously separated regions.
label: translocation

IAO_0000115: The 5' most coding exon.
label: five_prime_coding_exon

IAO_0000115: An exon that is bounded by 5' and 3' splice sites.
label: interior_exon

IAO_0000115: The coding exon that is most 3-prime on a given transcript.
label: three_prime_coding_exon

IAO_0000115: Messenger RNA sequences that are untranslated and lie five prime or three prime to sequences which are translated.
label: UTR

IAO_0000115: A region at the 5' end of a mature transcript (preceding the initiation codon) that is not translated into a protein.
label: five_prime_UTR

IAO_0000115: A region at the 3' end of a mature transcript (following the stop codon) that is not translated into a protein.
label: three_prime_UTR

IAO_0000115: A repetitive element, a few hundred base pairs long, that is dispersed throughout the genome. A common human SINE is the Alu element.
label: SINE_element

IAO_0000115: SSLP are a kind of sequence alteration where the number of repeated sequences in intergenic regions may differ.
label: simple_sequence_length_variation

IAO_0000115: A DNA transposable element defined as having termini with perfect, or nearly perfect short inverted repeats, generally 10 - 40 nucleotides long.
label: terminal_inverted_repeat_element

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a ribosomal RNA.
label: rRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a transfer RNA (SO:0000253).
label: tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding alanyl tRNA.
label: alanine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding arginyl tRNA (SO:0000255).
label: arginine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding asparaginyl tRNA (SO:0000256).
label: asparagine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding aspartyl tRNA (SO:0000257).
label: aspartic_acid_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding cysteinyl tRNA (SO:0000258).
label: cysteine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding glutaminyl tRNA (SO:0000260).
label: glutamic_acid_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding glutamyl tRNA (SO:0000260).
label: glutamine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding glycyl tRNA (SO:0000263).
label: glycine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding histidyl tRNA (SO:0000262).
label: histidine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding isoleucyl tRNA (SO:0000263).
label: isoleucine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding leucyl tRNA (SO:0000264).
label: leucine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding lysyl tRNA (SO:0000265).
label: lysine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding methionyl tRNA (SO:0000266).
label: methionine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding phenylalanyl tRNA (SO:0000267).
label: phenylalanine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding prolyl tRNA (SO:0000268).
label: proline_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding seryl tRNA (SO:000269).
label: serine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding tryptophanyl tRNA (SO:000271).
label: tryptophan_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding tyrosyl tRNA (SO:000272).
label: tyrosine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding valyl tRNA (SO:000273).
label: valine_tRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a small nuclear RNA (SO:0000274).
label: snRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a small nucleolar mRNA (SO:0000275).
label: snoRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A transcript which has undergone the necessary modifications, if any, for its function. In eukaryotes this includes, for example, processing of introns, cleavage, base modification, and modifications to the 5' and/or the 3' ends, other than addition of bases. In bacteria functional mRNAs are usually not modified.
comment: A processed transcript cannot contain introns.
label: mature_transcript

IAO_0000115: Messenger RNA is the intermediate molecule between DNA and protein. It includes UTR and coding sequences. It does not contain introns.
comment: An mRNA does not contain introns as it is a processed_transcript. The equivalent kind of primary_transcript is protein_coding_primary_transcript (SO:0000120) which may contain introns. This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: mRNA

IAO_0000115: A region of a nucleotide molecule that binds a Transcription Factor or Transcription Factor complex [GO:0005667].
label: TF_binding_site

IAO_0000115: The in-frame interval between the stop codons of a reading frame which when read as sequential triplets, has the potential of encoding a sequential string of amino acids. TER(NNN)nTER.
comment: The definition was modified by Rama. ORF is defined by the sequence, whereas the CDS is defined according to whether a polypeptide is made. This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: ORF

IAO_0000115: A transposable element with extensive secondary structure, characterized by large modular imperfect long inverted repeats.
label: foldback_element

IAO_0000115: The sequences extending on either side of a specific region.
label: flanking_region

IAO_0000115: A UTR bordered by the terminal and initial codons of two CDSs in a polycistronic transcript. Every UTR is either 5', 3' or internal.
label: internal_UTR

IAO_0000115: The untranslated sequence separating the 'cistrons' of multicistronic mRNA.
label: untranslated_region_polycistronic_mRNA

IAO_0000115: Sequence element that recruits a ribosomal subunit to internal mRNA for translation initiation.
label: internal_ribosome_entry_site

IAO_0000115: A attribute describing the addition of a poly A tail to the 3' end of a mRNA molecule.
label: polyadenylated

IAO_0000115: A kind of kind of sequence alteration where the copies of a region present varies across a population.
label: sequence_length_alteration

IAO_0000115: A post_transcriptionally modified base.
label: modified_RNA_base_feature

IAO_0000115: RNA that comprises part of a ribosome, and that can provide both structural scaffolding and catalytic activity.
label: rRNA

IAO_0000115: Transfer RNA (tRNA) molecules are approximately 80 nucleotides in length. Their secondary structure includes four short double-helical elements and three loops (D, anti-codon, and T loops). Further hydrogen bonds mediate the characteristic L-shaped molecular structure. Transfer RNAs have two regions of fundamental functional importance: the anti-codon, which is responsible for specific mRNA codon recognition, and the 3' end, to which the tRNA's corresponding amino acid is attached (by aminoacyl-tRNA synthetases). Transfer RNAs cope with the degeneracy of the genetic code in two manners: having more than one tRNA (with a specific anti-codon) for a particular amino acid; and 'wobble' base-pairing, i.e. permitting non-standard base-pairing at the 3rd anti-codon position.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has an alanine anticodon, and a 3' alanine binding region.
label: alanyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a small ribosomal subunit RNA.
label: rRNA_small_subunit_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has an asparagine anticodon, and a 3' asparagine binding region.
label: asparaginyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has an aspartic acid anticodon, and a 3' aspartic acid binding region.
label: aspartyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a cysteine anticodon, and a 3' cysteine binding region.
label: cysteinyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a glutamine anticodon, and a 3' glutamine binding region.
label: glutaminyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a glutamic acid anticodon, and a 3' glutamic acid binding region.
label: glutamyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a glycine anticodon, and a 3' glycine binding region.
label: glycyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a histidine anticodon, and a 3' histidine binding region.
label: histidyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has an isoleucine anticodon, and a 3' isoleucine binding region.
label: isoleucyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a leucine anticodon, and a 3' leucine binding region.
label: leucyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a lysine anticodon, and a 3' lysine binding region.
label: lysyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a methionine anticodon, and a 3' methionine binding region.
label: methionyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a phenylalanine anticodon, and a 3' phenylalanine binding region.
label: phenylalanyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a proline anticodon, and a 3' proline binding region.
label: prolyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a serine anticodon, and a 3' serine binding region.
label: seryl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a threonine anticodon, and a 3' threonine binding region.
label: threonyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a tryptophan anticodon, and a 3' tryptophan binding region.
label: tryptophanyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a tyrosine anticodon, and a 3' tyrosine binding region.
label: tyrosyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A tRNA sequence that has a valine anticodon, and a 3' valine binding region.
label: valyl_tRNA

IAO_0000115: A small nuclear RNA molecule involved in pre-mRNA splicing and processing.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: snRNA

IAO_0000115: A snoRNA (small nucleolar RNA) is any one of a class of small RNAs that are associated with the eukaryotic nucleus as components of small nucleolar ribonucleoproteins. They participate in the processing or modifications of many RNAs, mostly ribosomal RNAs (rRNAs) though snoRNAs are also known to target other classes of RNA, including spliceosomal RNAs, tRNAs, and mRNAs via a stretch of sequence that is complementary to a sequence in the targeted RNA.
label: snoRNA

IAO_0000115: Small, ~22-nt, RNA molecule that is the endogenous transcript of a miRNA gene (or the product of other non coding RNA genes. Micro RNAs are produced from precursor molecules (SO:0000647) that can form local hairpin structures, which ordinarily are processed (usually via the Dicer pathway) such that a single miRNA molecule accumulates from one arm of a hairpin precursor molecule. Micro RNAs may trigger the cleavage of their target molecules or act as translational repressors.
label: miRNA

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a sequence that is bound by another molecule.
comment: Formerly called transcript_by_bound_factor.
label: bound_by_factor

IAO_0000115: A transcript that is bound by a nucleic acid.
comment: Formerly called transcript_by_bound_nucleic_acid.
label: transcript_bound_by_nucleic_acid

IAO_0000115: A transcript that is bound by a protein.
comment: Formerly called transcript_by_bound_protein.
label: transcript_bound_by_protein

IAO_0000115: A gene that is engineered.
label: engineered_gene

IAO_0000115: A gene that is engineered and foreign.
label: engineered_foreign_gene

IAO_0000115: An mRNA with a minus 1 frameshift.
label: mRNA_with_minus_1_frameshift

IAO_0000115: A transposable_element that is engineered and foreign.
label: engineered_foreign_transposable_element_gene

IAO_0000115: The recognition site is bipartite and interrupted.
label: type_I_enzyme_restriction_site

IAO_0000115: A gene that is foreign.
label: foreign_gene

IAO_0000115: A sequence directly repeated at both ends of a defined sequence, of the sort typically found in retroviruses.
label: long_terminal_repeat

IAO_0000115: A gene that is a fusion.
label: fusion_gene

IAO_0000115: A fusion gene that is engineered.
label: engineered_fusion_gene

IAO_0000115: A repeat_region containing repeat_units of 2 to 10 bp repeated in tandem.
label: microsatellite

IAO_0000115: A repetitive element that is engineered and foreign.
label: engineered_foreign_repetitive_element

IAO_0000115: The sequence is complementarily repeated on the opposite strand. It is a palindrome, and it may, or may not be hyphenated. Examples: GCTGATCAGC, or GCTGA-----TCAGC.
label: inverted_repeat

IAO_0000115: A type of spliceosomal intron spliced by the U12 spliceosome, that includes U11, U12, U4atac/U6atac and U5 snRNAs.
comment: May have either GT-AC or AT-AC 5' and 3' boundaries.
label: U12_intron

IAO_0000115: A region of nucleic acid from which replication initiates; includes sequences that are recognized by replication proteins, the site from which the first separation of complementary strands occurs, and specific replication start sites.
label: origin_of_replication

IAO_0000115: Displacement loop; a region within mitochondrial DNA in which a short stretch of RNA is paired with one strand of DNA, displacing the original partner DNA strand in this region; also used to describe the displacement of a region of one strand of duplex DNA by a single stranded invader in the reaction catalyzed by RecA protein.
label: D_loop

hasExactSynonym: vertebrate immune system gene recombination feature
label: vertebrate_immune_system_gene_recombination_feature

IAO_0000115: Recombination signal including J-heptamer, J-spacer and J-nonamer in 5' of J-region of a J-gene or J-sequence.
label: J_gene_recombination_feature

IAO_0000115: Part of the primary transcript that is clipped off during processing.
label: clip

IAO_0000115: The recognition site is either palindromic, partially palindromic or an interrupted palindrome. Cleavage occurs within the recognition site.
label: type_II_enzyme_restriction_site

IAO_0000115: A modified nucleotide, i.e. a nucleotide other than A, T, C. G.
comment: Modified base:<modified_base>.
label: modified_DNA_base

IAO_0000115: A nucleotide modified by methylation.
label: methylated_DNA_base_feature

IAO_0000115: Regions of a few hundred to a few thousand bases in vertebrate genomes that are relatively GC and CpG rich; they are typically unmethylated and often found near the 5' ends of genes.
label: CpG_island

comment: similar to:<sequence_id>
label: computed_feature_by_similarity

IAO_0000115: Attribute to describe a feature that has been experimentally verified.
label: experimentally_determined

IAO_0000115: A double-helical region of nucleic acid formed by base-pairing between adjacent (inverted) complementary sequences.
label: stem_loop

IAO_0000115: A repeat where the same sequence is repeated in the same direction. Example: GCTGA-followed by-GCTGA.
label: direct_repeat

IAO_0000115: The first base where RNA polymerase begins to synthesize the RNA transcript.
label: TSS

IAO_0000115: A contiguous sequence which begins with, and includes, a start codon and ends with, and includes, a stop codon.
label: CDS

IAO_0000115: Complementary DNA; A piece of DNA copied from an mRNA and spliced into a vector for propagation in a suitable host.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: cDNA_clone

IAO_0000115: First codon to be translated by a ribosome.
label: start_codon

IAO_0000115: In mRNA, a set of three nucleotides that indicates the end of information for protein synthesis.
label: stop_codon

IAO_0000115: Sequences within the intron that modulate splice site selection for some introns.
label: intronic_splice_enhancer

IAO_0000115: An mRNA with a plus 1 frameshift.
label: mRNA_with_plus_1_frameshift

IAO_0000115: The first base to be translated into protein.
label: coding_start

IAO_0000115: A nucleotide sequence that may be used to identify a larger sequence.
label: tag

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a large ribosomal subunit RNA.
label: rRNA_large_subunit_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A short diagnostic sequence tag, serial analysis of gene expression (SAGE), that allows the quantitative and simultaneous analysis of a large number of transcripts.
label: SAGE_tag

IAO_0000115: The last base to be translated into protein. It does not include the stop codon.
label: coding_end

IAO_0000115: An mRNA with a plus 2 frameshift.
label: mRNA_with_plus_2_frameshift

IAO_0000115: Region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.
label: conserved_region

IAO_0000115: Short (typically a few hundred base pairs) DNA sequence that has a single occurrence in a genome and whose location and base sequence are known.
label: STS

IAO_0000115: Coding region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.
label: coding_conserved_region

IAO_0000115: The boundary between two exons in a processed transcript.
label: exon_junction

IAO_0000115: Non-coding region of sequence similarity by descent from a common ancestor.
label: nc_conserved_region

IAO_0000115: A mRNA with a minus 2 frameshift.
label: mRNA_with_minus_2_frameshift

IAO_0000115: A sequence that closely resembles a known functional gene, at another locus within a genome, that is non-functional as a consequence of (usually several) mutations that prevent either its transcription or translation (or both). In general, pseudogenes result from either reverse transcription of a transcript of their "normal" paralog (SO:0000043) (in which case the pseudogene typically lacks introns and includes a poly(A) tail) or from recombination (SO:0000044) (in which case the pseudogene is typically a tandem duplication of its "normal" paralog).
label: pseudogene

IAO_0000115: A double stranded RNA duplex, at least 20bp long, used experimentally to inhibit gene function by RNA interference.
label: RNAi_reagent

IAO_0000115: A highly repetitive and short (100-500 base pair) transposable element with terminal inverted repeats (TIR) and target site duplication (TSD). MITEs do not encode proteins.
label: MITE

IAO_0000115: A region in a genome which promotes recombination.
label: recombination_hotspot

IAO_0000115: Structural unit composed of a nucleic acid molecule which controls its own replication through the interaction of specific proteins at one or more origins of replication.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: chromosome

IAO_0000115: A cytologically distinguishable feature of a chromosome, often made visible by staining, and usually alternating light and dark.
label: chromosome_band

IAO_0000115: A region of sequence, aligned to another sequence with some statistical significance, using an algorithm such as BLAST or SIM4.
label: match

IAO_0000115: Region of a transcript that regulates splicing.
label: splice_enhancer

IAO_0000115: A tag produced from a single sequencing read from a cDNA clone or PCR product; typically a few hundred base pairs long.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: EST

IAO_0000115: A match against a nucleotide sequence.
label: nucleotide_match

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to repeating units. The forms found in nature are deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA), where the repeating units are 2-deoxy-D-ribose rings connected to a phosphate backbone, and ribonucleic acid (RNA), where the repeating units are D-ribose rings connected to a phosphate backbone.
label: nucleic_acid

IAO_0000115: A match against a protein sequence.
label: protein_match

IAO_0000115: An inversion site found on the Saccharomyces cerevisiae 2 micron plasmid.
label: FRT_site

IAO_0000115: An attribute to decide a sequence of nucleotides, nucleotide analogs, or amino acids that has been designed by an experimenter and which may, or may not, correspond with any natural sequence.
label: synthetic_sequence

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to a repeating unit made of a 2-deoxy-D-ribose ring connected to a phosphate backbone.
label: DNA

IAO_0000115: A sequence of nucleotides that has been algorithmically derived from an alignment of two or more different sequences.
label: sequence_assembly

IAO_0000115: A region of intronic nucleotide sequence targeted by a nuclease enzyme.
hasExactSynonym: group 1 intron homing endonuclease target region
label: group_1_intron_homing_endonuclease_target_region

IAO_0000115: A region of the genome which is co-inherited as the result of the lack of historic recombination within it.
label: haplotype_block

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a sequence consisting of nucleobases bound to a repeating unit made of a D-ribose ring connected to a phosphate backbone.
comment: This term is mapped to MGED. Do not obsolete without consulting MGED ontology.
label: RNA

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing a region that is bounded either side by a particular kind of region.
label: flanked

IAO_0000115: An attribute describing sequence that is flanked by Lox-P sites.
label: floxed

IAO_0000115: A set of (usually) three nucleotide bases in a DNA or RNA sequence, which together code for a unique amino acid or the termination of translation and are contained within the CDS.
label: codon

IAO_0000115: An attribute to describe sequence that is flanked by the FLP recombinase recognition site, FRT.
label: FRT_flanked

IAO_0000115: A cDNA clone constructed from more than one mRNA. Usually an experimental artifact.
label: invalidated_by_chimeric_cDNA

IAO_0000115: A transgene that is floxed.
label: floxed_gene

IAO_0000115: The region of sequence surrounding a transposable element.
label: transposable_element_flanking_region

IAO_0000115: A region encoding an integrase which acts at a site adjacent to it (attI_site) to insert DNA which must include but is not limited to an attC_site.
label: integron

IAO_0000115: The junction where an insertion occurred.
label: insertion_site

IAO_0000115: A region within an integron, adjacent to an integrase, at which site specific recombination involving an attC_site takes place.
label: attI_site

IAO_0000115: The junction in a genome where a transposable_element has inserted.
label: transposable_element_insertion_site

IAO_0000115: A non-coding RNA less than 200 nucleotides long, usually with a specific secondary structure, that acts to regulate gene expression. These include short ncRNAs such as piRNA, miRNA and siRNAs (among others).
label: small_regulatory_ncRNA

IAO_0000115: A transposon that encodes function required for conjugation.
label: conjugative_transposon

IAO_0000115: An RNA sequence that has catalytic activity with or without an associated ribonucleoprotein.
comment: This was moved to be a child of transcript (SO:0000673) because some enzymatic RNA regions are part of primary transcripts and some are part of processed transcripts.
label: enzymatic_RNA

IAO_0000115: A recombinationally rearranged gene by inversion.
label: recombinationally_inverted_gene

IAO_0000115: An RNA with catalytic activity.
label: ribozyme

IAO_0000115: 5_8S ribosomal RNA (5. 8S rRNA) is a component of the large subunit of the eukaryotic ribosome. It is transcribed by RNA polymerase I as part of the 45S precursor that also contains 18S and 28S rRNA. Functionally, it is thought that 5.8S rRNA may be involved in ribosome translocation. It is also known to form covalent linkage to the p53 tumour suppressor protein. 5_8S rRNA is also found in archaea.
label: rRNA_5_8S

IAO_0000115: A small (184-nt in E. coli) RNA that forms a hairpin type structure. 6S RNA associates with RNA polymerase in a highly specific manner. 6S RNA represses expression from a sigma70-dependent promoter during stationary phase.
label: RNA_6S

IAO_0000115: An enterobacterial RNA that binds the CsrA protein. The CsrB RNAs contain a conserved motif CAGGXXG that is found in up to 18 copies and has been suggested to bind CsrA. The Csr regulatory system has a strong negative regulatory effect on glycogen biosynthesis, glyconeogenesis and glycogen catabolism and a positive regulatory effect on glycolysis. In other bacteria such as Erwinia caratovara the RsmA protein has been shown to regulate the production of virulence determinants, such extracellular enzymes. RsmA binds to RsmB regulatory RNA which is also a member of this family.
label: CsrB_RsmB_RNA

IAO_0000115: DsrA RNA regulates both transcription, by overcoming transcriptional silencing by the nucleoid-associated H-NS protein, and translation, by promoting efficient translation of the stress sigma factor, RpoS. These two activities of DsrA can be separated by mutation: the first of three stem-loops of the 85 nucleotide RNA is necessary for RpoS translation but not for anti-H-NS action, while the second stem-loop is essential for antisilencing and less critical for RpoS translation. The third stem-loop, which behaves as a transcription terminator, can be substituted by the trp transcription terminator without loss of either DsrA function. The sequence of the first stem-loop of DsrA is complementary with the upstream leader portion of RpoS messenger RNA, suggesting that pairing of DsrA with the RpoS message might be important for translational regulation.
label: DsrA_RNA

IAO_0000115: A small untranslated RNA involved in expression of the dipeptide and oligopeptide transport systems in Escherichia coli.
label: GcvB_RNA

IAO_0000115: A small catalytic RNA motif that catalyzes self-cleavage reaction. Its name comes from its secondary structure which resembles a carpenter's hammer. The hammerhead ribozyme is involved in the replication of some viroid and some satellite RNAs.
label: hammerhead_ribozyme

IAO_0000115: A non-translated 93 nt antisense RNA that binds its target ompF mRNA and regulates ompF expression by inhibiting translation and inducing degradation of the message.
label: MicF_RNA

IAO_0000115: A small untranslated RNA which is induced in response to oxidative stress in Escherichia coli. Acts as a global regulator to activate or repress the expression of as many as 40 genes, including the fhlA-encoded transcriptional activator and the rpoS-encoded sigma(s) subunit of RNA polymerase. OxyS is bound by the Hfq protein, that increases the OxyS RNA interaction with its target messages.
label: OxyS_RNA

IAO_0000115: The RNA molecule essential for the catalytic activity of RNase MRP, an enzymatically active ribonucleoprotein with two distinct roles in eukaryotes. In mitochondria it plays a direct role in the initiation of mitochondrial DNA replication. In the nucleus it is involved in precursor rRNA processing, where it cleaves the internal transcribed spacer 1 between 18S and 5.8S rRNAs.
label: RNase_MRP_RNA

IAO_0000115: The RNA component of Ribonuclease P (RNase P), a ubiquitous endoribonuclease, found in archaea, bacteria and eukarya as well as chloroplasts and mitochondria. Its best characterized activity is the generation of mature 5 prime ends of tRNAs by cleaving the 5 prime leader elements of precursor-tRNAs. Cellular RNase Ps are ribonucleoproteins. RNA from bacterial RNase Ps retains its catalytic activity in the absence of the protein subunit, i.e. it is a ribozyme. Isolated eukaryotic and archaeal RNase P RNA has not been shown to retain its catalytic function, but is still essential for the catalytic activity of the holoenzyme. Although the archaeal and eukaryotic holoenzymes have a much greater protein content than the bacterial ones, the RNA cores from all the three lineages are homologous. Helices corresponding to P1, P2, P3, P4, and P10/11 are common to all cellular RNase P RNAs. Yet, there is considerable sequence variation, particularly among the eukaryotic RNAs.
label: RNase_P_RNA

IAO_0000115: Translational regulation of the stationary phase sigma factor RpoS is mediated by the formation of a double-stranded RNA stem-loop structure in the upstream region of the rpoS messenger RNA, occluding the translation initiation site. Clones carrying rprA (RpoS regulator RNA) increased the translation of RpoS. The rprA gene encodes a 106 nucleotide regulatory RNA. As with DsrA Rfam:RF00014, RprA is predicted to form three stem-loops. Thus, at least two small RNAs, DsrA and RprA, participate in the positive regulation of RpoS translation. Unlike DsrA, RprA does not have an extensive region of complementarity to the RpoS leader, leaving its mechanism of action unclear. RprA is non-essential.
label: RprA_RNA

IAO_0000115: The Rev response element (RRE) is encoded within the HIV-env gene. Rev is an essential regulatory protein of HIV that binds an internal loop of the RRE leading, encouraging further Rev-RRE binding. This RNP complex is critical for mRNA export and hence for expression of the HIV structural proteins.
label: RRE_RNA

IAO_0000115: A 109-nucleotide RNA of E. coli that seems to have a regulatory role on the galactose operon. Changes in Spot 42 levels are implicated in affecting DNA polymerase I levels.
label: spot_42_RNA

IAO_0000115: The RNA component of telomerase, a reverse transcriptase that synthesizes telomeric DNA.
label: telomerase_RNA

IAO_0000115: U1 is a small nuclear RNA (snRNA) component of the spliceosome (involved in pre-mRNA splicing). Its 5' end forms complementary base pairs with the 5' splice junction, thus defining the 5' donor site of an intron. There are significant differences in sequence and secondary structure between metazoan and yeast U1 snRNAs, the latter being much longer (568 nucleotides as compared to 164 nucleotides in human). Nevertheless, secondary structure predictions suggest that all U1 snRNAs share a 'common core' consisting of helices I, II, the proximal region of III, and IV.
label: U1_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U2 is a small nuclear RNA (snRNA) component of the spliceosome (involved in pre-mRNA splicing). Complementary binding between U2 snRNA (in an area lying towards the 5' end but 3' to hairpin I) and the branchpoint sequence (BPS) of the intron results in the bulging out of an unpaired adenine, on the BPS, which initiates a nucleophilic attack at the intronic 5' splice site, thus starting the first of two transesterification reactions that mediate splicing.
label: U2_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U4 small nuclear RNA (U4 snRNA) is a component of the major U2-dependent spliceosome. It forms a duplex with U6, and with each splicing round, it is displaced from U6 (and the spliceosome) in an ATP-dependent manner, allowing U6 to refold and create the active site for splicing catalysis. A recycling process involving protein Prp24 re-anneals U4 and U6.
label: U4_snRNA

IAO_0000115: An snRNA required for the splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns. It forms a base paired complex with U6atac_snRNA (SO:0000397).
label: U4atac_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U5 RNA is a component of both types of known spliceosome. The precise function of this molecule is unknown, though it is known that the 5' loop is required for splice site selection and p220 binding, and that both the 3' stem-loop and the Sm site are important for Sm protein binding and cap methylation.
label: U5_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U6 snRNA is a component of the spliceosome which is involved in splicing pre-mRNA. The putative secondary structure consensus base pairing is confined to a short 5' stem loop, but U6 snRNA is thought to form extensive base-pair interactions with U4 snRNA.
label: U6_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U6atac_snRNA is an snRNA required for the splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns. It forms a base paired complex with U4atac_snRNA (SO:0000394).
label: U6atac_snRNA

IAO_0000115: U11 snRNA plays a role in splicing of the minor U12-dependent class of eukaryotic nuclear introns, similar to U1 snRNA in the major class spliceosome it base pairs to the conserved 5' splice site sequence.
label: U11_snRNA

IAO_0000115: The U12 small nuclear (snRNA), together with U4atac/U6atac, U5, and U11 snRNAs and associated proteins, forms a spliceosome that cleaves a divergent class of low-abundance pre-mRNA introns.
label: U12_snRNA

IAO_0000115: An attribute describes a quality of sequence.
label: sequence_attribute

IAO_0000115: U14 small nucleolar RNA (U14 snoRNA) is required for early cleavages of eukaryotic precursor rRNAs. In yeasts, this molecule possess a stem-loop region (known as the Y-domain) which is essential for function. A similar structure, but with a different consensus sequence, is found in plants, but is absent in vertebrates.
comment: An evolutionarily conserved eukaryotic low molecular weight RNA capable of intermolecular hybridization with both homologous and heterologous 18S rRNA.
label: U14_snoRNA

IAO_0000115: A family of RNAs are found as part of the enigmatic vault ribonucleoprotein complex. The complex consists of a major vault protein (MVP), two minor vault proteins (VPARP and TEP1), and several small untranslated RNA molecules. It has been suggested that the vault complex is involved in drug resistance.
label: vault_RNA

IAO_0000115: Y RNAs are components of the Ro ribonucleoprotein particle (Ro RNP), in association with Ro60 and La proteins. The Y RNAs and Ro60 and La proteins are well conserved, but the function of the Ro RNP is not known. In humans the RNA component can be one of four small RNAs: hY1, hY3, hY4 and hY5. These small RNAs are predicted to fold into a conserved secondary structure containing three stem structures. The largest of the four, hY1, contains an additional hairpin.
label: Y_RNA

IAO_0000115: An intron within an intron. Twintrons are group II or III introns, into which another group II or III intron has been transposed.
label: twintron

IAO_0000115: Group I catalytic introns are large self-splicing ribozymes. They catalyze their own excision from mRNA, tRNA and rRNA precursors in a wide range of organisms. The core secondary structure consists of 9 paired regions (P1-P9). These fold to essentially two domains, the P4-P6 domain (formed from the stacking of P5, P4, P6 and P6a helices) and the P3-P9 domain (formed from the P8, P3, P7 and P9 helices). Group I catalytic introns often have long ORFs inserted in loop regions.
label: group_I_intron

IAO_0000115: The signal recognition particle (SRP) is a universally conserved ribonucleoprotein. It is involved in the co-translational targeting of proteins to membranes. The eukaryotic SRP consists of a 300-nucleotide 7S RNA and six proteins: SRPs 72, 68, 54, 19, 14, and 9. Archaeal SRP consists of a 7S RNA and homologues of the eukaryotic SRP19 and SRP54 proteins. In most eubacteria, the SRP consists of a 4.5S RNA and the Ffh protein (a homologue of the eukaryotic SRP54 protein). Eukaryotic and archaeal 7S RNAs have very similar secondary structures, with eight helical elements. These fold into the Alu and S domains, separated by a long linker region. Eubacterial SRP is generally a simpler structure, with the M domain of Ffh bound to a region of the 4.5S RNA that corresponds to helix 8 of the eukaryotic and archaeal SRP S domain. Some Gram-positive bacteria (e.g. Bacillus subtilis), however, have a larger SRP RNA that also has an Alu domain. The Alu domain is thought to mediate the peptide chain elongation retardation function of the SRP. The universally conserved helix which interacts with the SRP54/Ffh M domain mediates signal sequence recognition. In eukaryotes and archaea, the SRP19-helix 6 complex is thought to be involved in SRP assembly and stabilizes helix 8 for SRP54 binding.
label: SRP_RNA

IAO_0000115: A tertiary structure in RNA where nucleotides in a loop form base pairs with a region of RNA downstream of the loop.
label: pseudoknot

IAO_0000115: A pseudoknot which contains two stems and at least two loops.
label: H_pseudoknot

IAO_0000115: Most box C/D snoRNAs also contain long (>10 nt) sequences complementary to rRNA. Boxes C and D, as well as boxes C' and D', are usually located in close proximity, and form a structure known as the box C/D motif. This motif is important for snoRNA stability, processing, nucleolar targeting and function. A small number of box C/D snoRNAs are involved in rRNA processing; most, however, are known or predicted to serve as guide RNAs in ribose methylation of rRNA. Targeting involves direct base pairing of the snoRNA at the rRNA site to be modified and selection of a rRNA nucleotide a fixed distance from box D or D'.
label: C_D_box_snoRNA

IAO_0000115: Members of the box H/ACA family contain an ACA triplet, exactly 3 nt upstream from the 3' end and an H-box in a hinge region that links two structurally similar functional domains of the molecule. Both boxes are important for snoRNA biosynthesis and function. A few box H/ACA snoRNAs are involved in rRNA processing; most others are known or predicted to participate in selection of uridine nucleosides in rRNA to be converted to pseudouridines. Site selection is mediated by direct base pairing of the snoRNA with rRNA through one or both targeting domains.
label: H_ACA_box_snoRNA

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a small nucleolar RNA of the box C/D family.
label: C_D_box_snoRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a small nucleolar RNA of the box H/ACA family.
hasExactSynonym: H ACA box snoRNA primary transcript
label: H_ACA_box_snoRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: The insertion and deletion of uridine (U) residues, usually within coding regions of mRNA transcripts of cryptogenes in the mitochondrial genome of kinetoplastid protozoa.
label: transcript_edited_by_U_insertion/deletion

IAO_0000115: A short 3'-uridylated RNA that can form a duplex (except for its post-transcriptionally added oligo_U tail (SO:0000609)) with a stretch of mature edited mRNA.
label: guide_RNA

IAO_0000115: Group II introns are found in rRNA, tRNA and mRNA of organelles in fungi, plants and protists, and also in mRNA in bacteria. They are large self-splicing ribozymes and have 6 structural domains (usually designated dI to dVI). A subset of group II introns also encode essential splicing proteins in intronic ORFs. The length of these introns can therefore be up to 3kb. Splicing occurs in almost identical fashion to nuclear pre-mRNA splicing with two transesterification steps. The 2' hydroxyl of a bulged adenosine in domain VI attacks the 5' splice site, followed by nucleophilic attack on the 3' splice site by the 3' OH of the upstream exon. Protein machinery is required for splicing in vivo, and long range intron to intron and intron-exon interactions are important for splice site positioning. Group II introns are further sub-classified into groups IIA and IIB which differ in splice site consensus, distance of bulged A from 3' splice site, some tertiary interactions, and intronic ORF phylogeny.
label: group_II_intron

IAO_0000115: Edited mRNA sequence mediated by a single guide RNA (SO:0000602).
label: editing_block

IAO_0000115: A region containing or overlapping no genes that is bounded on either side by a gene, or bounded by a gene and the end of the chromosome.

IAO_0000115: Sequence of about 100 nucleotides of A added to the 3' end of most eukaryotic mRNAs.

IAO_0000115: A pyrimidine rich sequence near the 3' end of an intron to which the 5'end becomes covalently bound during nuclear splicing. The resulting structure resembles a lariat.

IAO_0000115: A variably distant linear promoter region recognized by TFIIIC, with consensus sequence AGGTTCCAnnCC.

IAO_0000115: A repeat region containing tandemly repeated sequences having a unit length of 10 to 40 bp.
label: minisatellite

IAO_0000115: Antisense RNA is RNA that is transcribed from the coding, rather than the template, strand of DNA. It is therefore complementary to mRNA.

IAO_0000115: The reverse complement of the primary transcript.

SRNAs trigger the cleavage of their target molecules.

IAO_0000115: A primary transcript encoding a micro RNA.
label: miRNA_primary_transcript

IAO_0000115: Ribosomal RNA transcript that structures the small subunit of the ribosome.

IAO_0000115: 5S ribosomal RNA (5S rRNA) is a component of the large ribosomal subunit in both prokaryotes and eukaryotes. In eukaryotes, it is synthesised by RNA polymerase III (the other eukaryotic rRNAs are cleaved from a 45S precursor synthesised by RNA polymerase I). In Xenopus oocytes, it has been shown that fingers 4-7 of the nine-zinc finger transcription factor TFIIIA can bind to the central region of 5S RNA. Thus, in addition to positively regulating 5S rRNA transcription, TFIIIA also stabilizes 5S rRNA until it is required for transcription.

IAO_0000115: A region of sequence containing one or more repeat units.

IAO_0000115: A gene encoding an mRNA that has the stop codon redefined as selenocysteine.

IAO_0000115: An adaptive island is a genomic island that provides an adaptive advantage to the host.
comment: The iron-uptake ability of many pathogens are conveyed by adaptive islands. Nature Reviews Microbiology 2, 414-424 (2004); doi:10.1038 micro 884 GENOMIC ISLANDS IN PATHOGENIC AND ENVIRONMENTAL MICROORGANISMS Ulrich Dobrindt, Bianca Hochhut, Ute Hentschel & Jorg Hacker.

IAO_0000115: An edit to insert a GC dinucleotide.
comment: The type of RNA editing found in the mitochondria of Myxomycota, characterized by the insertion of mono- and dinucleotides in RNAs relative to their mtDNA template and in addition, C to U base conversion. The most common mononucleotide insertion is cytidine, although a number of uridine mononucleotides are inserted at specific sites. Adenine and guanine have not been observed in mononucleotide insertions. Five different dinucleotide insertions have been observed, GC, GU, CU, AU and AA. Both mono- and dinucleotide insertions create open reading frames in mRNA and contribute to highly conserved structural features of rRNAs and tRNAs.
label: insert_GC

IAO_0000115: A motif of five consecutive residues and two H-bonds in which: Residue(i) is Aspartate or Asparagine (Asx), side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2) or (i+3), main-chain CO of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3) or (i+4).
label: asx_motif

IAO_0000115: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet in which the main chains of two consecutive residues are H-bonded to that of the third, and in which the dihedral angles are as follows: Residue(i): -140 degrees < phi(l) -20 degrees , -90 degrees < psi(l) < 40 degrees. Residue (i+1): -180 degrees < phi < -25 degrees or +120 degrees < phi < +180 degrees, +40 degrees < psi < +180 degrees or -180 degrees < psi < -120 degrees.
label: beta_bulge

IAO_0000115: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet consisting of two H-bonds. Beta bulge loops often occur at the loop ends of beta-hairpins.
label: beta_bulge_loop

IAO_0000115: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet consisting of two H-bonds in which: the main-chain NH of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain CO of residue(i+4), the main-chain CO of residue i is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3), these loops have an RL nest at residues i+2 and i+3.
label: beta_bulge_loop_five

IAO_0000115: A motif of three residues within a beta-sheet consisting of two H-bonds in which: the main-chain NH of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain CO of residue(i+5), the main-chain CO of residue i is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+4), these loops have an RL nest at residues i+3 and i+4.
label: beta_bulge_loop_six

IAO_0000115: A beta strand describes a single length of polypeptide chain that forms part of a beta sheet. A single continuous stretch of amino acids adopting an extended conformation of hydrogen bonds between the N-O and the C=O of another part of the peptide. This forms a secondary protein structure in which two or more extended polypeptide regions are hydrogen-bonded to one another in a planar array.
comment: Range.
label: beta_strand

IAO_0000115: A peptide region which hydrogen bonded to another region of peptide running in the oposite direction (one running N-terminal to C-terminal and one running C-terminal to N-terminal). Hydrogen bonding occurs between every other C=O from one strand to every other N-H on the adjacent strand. In this case, if two atoms C-alpha (i) and C-alpha (j) are adjacent in two hydrogen-bonded beta strands, then they form two mutual backbone hydrogen bonds to each other's flanking peptide groups; this is known as a close pair of hydrogen bonds. The peptide backbone dihedral angles (phi, psi) are about (-140 degrees, 135 degrees) in antiparallel sheets.
comment: Range.
label: antiparallel_beta_strand

IAO_0000115: A peptide region which hydrogen bonded to another region of peptide running in the oposite direction (both running N-terminal to C-terminal). This orientation is slightly less stable because it introduces nonplanarity in the inter-strand hydrogen bonding pattern. Hydrogen bonding occurs between every other C=O from one strand to every other N-H on the adjacent strand. In this case, if two atoms C-alpha (i)and C-alpha (j) are adjacent in two hydrogen-bonded beta strands, then they do not hydrogen bond to each other; rather, one residue forms hydrogen bonds to the residues that flank the other (but not vice versa). For example, residue i may form hydrogen bonds to residues j - 1 and j + 1; this is known as a wide pair of hydrogen bonds. By contrast, residue j may hydrogen-bond to different residues altogether, or to none at all. The dihedral angles (phi, psi) are about (-120 degrees, 115 degrees) in parallel sheets.
comment: Range.
label: parallel_beta_strand

IAO_0000115: A helix is a secondary_structure conformation where the peptide backbone forms a coil.
comment: Range.
label: peptide_helix

IAO_0000115: A left handed helix is a region of peptide where the coiled conformation turns in an anticlockwise, left handed screw.
label: left_handed_peptide_helix

IAO_0000115: A right handed helix is a region of peptide where the coiled conformation turns in a clockwise, right handed screw.

IAO_0000115: The helix has 3.6 residues per turn which corresponds to a translation of 1.5 angstroms (= 0.15 nm) along the helical axis. Every backbone N-H group donates a hydrogen bond to the backbone C=O group of the amino acid four residues earlier.
comment: Range.
label: alpha_helix

IAO_0000115: The pi helix has 4.1 residues per turn and a translation of 1.15  (=0.115 nm) along the helical axis. The N-H group of an amino acid forms a hydrogen bond with the C=O group of the amino acid five residues earlier.
comment: Range.
label: pi_helix

IAO_0000115: The 3-10 helix has 3 residues per turn with a translation of 2.0 angstroms (=0.2 nm) along the helical axis. The N-H group of an amino acid forms a hydrogen bond with the C=O group of the amino acid three residues earlier.

label: three_ten_helix

IAO_0000115: A motif of two consecutive residues with dihedral angles: Residue(i): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees, -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees. Residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees, -40 degrees < psi < +90 degrees.

IAO_0000115: Common Type: A motif of six consecutive residues that contains two H-bonds in which: the main-chain CO of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+5) the main-chain CO of residue(i+1) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+4).
label: schellmann_loop_six

IAO_0000115: A motif of five consecutive residues and two hydrogen bonds in which: residue(i) is Serine (S) or Threonine (T), the side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2) or (i+3) , the main-chain CO group of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+3) or (i+4).

IAO_0000115: A motif of four or five consecutive residues and one H-bond in which: residue(i) is Serine (S) or Threonine (T), the side-chain OH of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain CO of residue(i3) or (i4), Phi angles of residues(i1), (i2) and (i3) are negative.

hasExactSynonym: asx turn right handed type two
label: asx_turn_right_handed_type_two

IAO_0000115: Right handed type I (dihedral angles):- Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi (1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees, -90 degrees < psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees. Residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees, -90 degrees < psi < +40 degrees.
hasExactSynonym: asx turn type right handed type one

IAO_0000115: Left handed type I:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond, which, if present, is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. IAO_0000115: Right handed type I:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond, which, if present, is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. hasExactSynonym: beta turn right handed type one

IAO_0000115: Right handed type II:A motif of four consecutive residues that may contain one H-bond, which, if present, is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth. IAO_0000115: A motif of three consecutive residues and one H-bond in which: residue(i) is Serine (S) or Threonine (T), the side-chain O of residue(i) is H-bonded to the main-chain NH of residue(i+2).

IAO_0000115: The peptide twists in an anticlockwise, left handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees, -90 degrees psi +120 degrees < +40 degrees, residue(i+1): -140 degrees < phi < -20 degrees, -90 < psi < +40 degrees.

IAO_0000115: The peptide twists in an anticlockwise, left handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees, +80 degrees psi +120 degrees < +180 degrees, residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees, -40 < psi < +90 degrees.

hasExactSynonym: st turn right handed type one

IAO_0000115: The peptide twists in an clockwise, right handed manner. The dihedral angles for this turn are: Residue(i): -140 degrees < chi(1) -120 degrees < -20 degrees, +80 degrees psi +120 degrees < +180 degrees, residue(i+1): +20 degrees < phi < +140 degrees, -40 < psi < +90 degrees.
hasExactSynonym: st turn right handed type two

IAO_0000115: A site of sequence variation (alteration). Alternative sequence due to naturally occurring events such as polymorphisms and alternative splicing or experimental methods such as site directed mutagenesis.

IAO_0000115: A motif of four consecutive peptide residues that may contain one H-bond, which, if present, is between the main-chain CO of the first residue and the main-chain NH of the fourth and is characterized by the dihedral angles: Residue(i+1): phi ~ -60 degrees, psi ~ -30 degrees. Residue(i+2): phi ~ -120 degrees, psi ~ 120 degrees.

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, located immediately upstream of some TATA box elements with respect to the TSS (+1). Consensus sequence is YGGTCACACTR. Marked spatial preference within core promoter; tend to occur near the TSS, although not as tightly as INR (SO:0000014).

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, usually located between -60 and +1 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is AWCAGCTGWT. Tends to co-occur with DMv2 (SO:0001161). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015).

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, usually located between -50 and -10 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is KTYRGTATWTTT. Tends to co-occur with DMv4 (SO:0001157) . Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or MTE (SO:0001162).
label: DMv5_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, usually located between -30 and +15 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is KNNCAKCNCTRNY. Tends to co-occur with DMv2 (SO:0001161). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or MTE (0001162).
label: DMv3_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, usually located between -60 and -45 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is MKSYGGCARCGSYSS. Tends to co-occur with DMv3 (SO:0001160). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or MTE (SO:0001162).
label: DMv2_motif

IAO_0000115: A sequence element characteristic of some RNA polymerase II promoters, usually located between +20 and +30 relative to the TSS. Consensus sequence is CSARCSSAACGS. Tends to co-occur with INR motif (SO:0000014). Tends to not occur with DPE motif (SO:0000015) or DMv5 (SO:0001159).

IAO_0000115: A promoter motif with consensus sequence TCATTCG.
